I believe this is a bug. I've set `app.response_class = MyCustomResponseClass`, but this isn't being used when `handle_api_exception` is triggered.

The fix should be to simply change [this line](https://github.com/flask-api/flask-api/blob/028c1bfb3161b7c8cb14ad5c77d69fc31cde8b61/flask_api/app.py#L110) to read:

    return self.response_class({'message': exc.detail}, status=exc.status_code)

